{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01A9G6uHQeFCLYHHqQxmrgBD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now I have a clear picture:\n\n1. **cockroachdb namespace:**\n   - `crdb-cluster` (headless ClusterIP) - ports 26257/TCP, 8080/TCP\n   - `crdb-cluster-public` (ClusterIP: 10.96.179.82) - ports 26257/TCP, 8080/TCP\n   - Pods: crdb-cluster-0, crdb-cluster-1, crdb-cluster-2 (all Running)\n   - TLS secret: `crdb-ui-tls`\n\n2. **ingress-nginx namespace:**\n   - `ingress-nginx-controller` (LoadBalancer) - ports 80:30982/TCP, 443:32013/TCP\n   - ConfigMap `ingress-nginx-controller` (empty, 0 data)\n\nNow I need to set up the DB Console at https://crdb-ui.example.com by creating an Ingress resource that routes HTTPS traffic to port 8080 on the CockroachDB side, using the nginx ingress class and the existing TLS certificate.\n\nFor SQL traffic on port 26257, since CockroachDB uses raw TCP rather than HTTP, I'll need to configure ingress-nginx's TCP passthrough mode. This involves creating a `tcp-services` ConfigMap in the ingress-nginx namespace that maps port 26257 to the CockroachDB service, then patching the controller deployment to reference this ConfigMap and expose the port on the LoadBalancer service.\n\nThe DB Console itself runs on port 8080 with its own TLS, but the ingress will handle the external HTTPS termination. So I'll use the `backend-protocol: HTTPS` annotation to have ingress-nginx terminate client TLS with the crdb-ui-tls secret while connecting to the backend over HTTPS, which avoids the mismatch of sending plain HTTP to CockroachDB's HTTPS-only console. Now for the TCP SQL traffic on port 26257, I need to configure a ConfigMap for tcp-services in the ingress controller.\n\nWriting the Ingress resource...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":511,"cache_read_input_tokens":29577,"cache