{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01AH1pw1aETb24R2pERdNFaA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"CockroachDB is running in `--insecure` mode, so:\n- Port 8080 serves plain HTTP (not HTTPS)\n- Port 26257 accepts insecure SQL connections\n\nSo for the Ingress:\n- No need for `backend-protocol: HTTPS` - the backend is plain HTTP\n- Create Ingress with TLS (using `crdb-ui-tls` secret) terminating at nginx, forwarding plain HTTP to port 8080\n- The oracle hits port 80 with Host: crdb-ui.example.com, which would get a 301 redirect to HTTPS (which is 2xx/3xx, passes the check)\n- Even with ssl-redirect enabled, the 308 response still falls within the 200-399 range, so the health check passes regardless\n- I'll configure the Ingress to handle both HTTP and HTTPS, then set up the TCP services config for SQL connections\n- Now I need to patch the ingress-nginx controller Deployment to add the `--tcp-services-configmap` argument and expose port 26257 on both the Service and container, so the oracle's SQL check can connect to CockroachDB through the ingress controller\n\n.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1295,"cache_read_input_tokens":35448,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1295},"output_tokens":33,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eb566f54-c78f-4de5-a1f2-b99d1b95a953","uuid":"e38d621b-6bc5-495b-8428-354321962718","request_id":"req_011CbyGLv3MT76QdaSyCGVoK"}
